<br>
My note about chain mail being cheaper than plate was geared towards real life, not the game itself.  Back in the 'day', day being maybe around the Crusades or so, chain was the most popular armor in western Europe because it was much cheaper than plate mail.  Also, chain didn't need to be custom fitted.  The average templar or knight usually had to search for a months, even years, to find a suit of plate mail.  Chain could be distributed among troops without worry of pinched groins or concussion from an ill-fitting helmet.<br>
<br>
